    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 across all 5 operating points provides the required comparative assurance. Residual uncertainty in aleatory sources (blood donor variability, geometric tolerances) is acknowledged in the factor rationales and validation result narratives; the overall credibility evidence is judged adequate for the intended regulatory submission decision.",
